#include <ESP8266WiFi.h> #include <FirebaseESP8266.h> #include "DHT.h" // -------- WiFi -------- #define WIFI_SSID "YOUR_WIFI" #define WIFI_PASSWORD "YOUR_PASS" // -------- Firebase -------- #define FIREBASE_HOST "your-project.firebaseio.com" #define FIREBASE_AUTH "database-secret" // -------- Pins -------- #define DHTPIN D4 #define DHTTYPE DHT11 #define LED_PIN D5 #define BUZZER D6 DHT dht(DHTPIN, DHTTYPE); FirebaseData fb; // -------- Threshold -------- float tempLimit = 35; float humLimit = 70; unsigned long prevMillis = 0; void setup() {   Serial.begin(9600);   pinMode(LED_PIN, OUTPUT);   pinMode(BUZZER, OUTPUT);      dht.begin();   WiFi.begin(WIFI_SSID, WIFI_PASSWORD);   while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {     delay(500);     Serial.print(".");   }   Firebase.begin(FIREBASE_HOST, FIREBASE_AUTH); } void loop() {   // -------- Reconnect WiFi --------   if (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {     WiFi.begin(WIFI_SSID, WIFI_PASSWORD);   }   // -------- Push sensor data --------   if (millis() - prevMillis > 4000) {     prevMillis = millis();     float t = dht.readTemperature();     float h = dht.readHumidity();     Firebase.setFloat(fb, "/IoT_Node_1/sensor/temperature", t);     Firebase.setFloat(fb, "/IoT_Node_1/sensor/humidity", h);     // -------- Read LED control --------     Firebase.getInt(fb, "/IoT_Node_1/control/led");     int ledState = fb.intData();     digitalWrite(LED_PIN, ledState);     // -------- Threshold alert --------     if (t > tempLimit || h > humLimit) {       digitalWrite(BUZZER, HIGH);     } else {       digitalWrite(BUZZER, LOW);     }   } }

Ibrahim Alvan+91 99020 16694
The Smart Home Automation System is an IoT-based project designed to enable remote monitoring and control of home appliances using the internet. In this system, an ESP8266 (NodeMCU) microcontroller is used as the main controller, which connects to a Wi-Fi network and communicates with a cloud platform (Firebase Realtime Database). Users can control devices such as lights and alarms from anywhere by changing values on a web or mobile dashboard connected to Firebase. In this project, an LED is used to represent a smart light, and a buzzer is used to represent an alert or alarm system. The ESP8266 continuously reads the device states stored in Firebase and turns the LED and buzzer ON or OFF in real time based on user commands. This demonstrates bi-directional c
